  "text": "Measurement of TGF-␤1 and nitrate/nitrite levels. Renal tissue was homogenized in lysis buffer (10 mM Tris, pH 7.4, 100 mM NaCl, 1 mM EDTA, 20 mM Na 4P2O7, 2 mM Na3VO4, and 1% Triton X-100) containing 1:100 protease inhibitor cocktail (Sigma). Total (latent and active) TGF-␤1 protein levels in renal extracts were determined by ELISA (R&D Systems, Minneapolis, MN). Nitrate/nitrite levels (indicative of NO formation) in urine were measured by a fluorometric assay as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
